{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Fpg1gct31GoCcJx7QHhJ1d","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture:\n- CA cert: stored in `mongodb-tls-ca` secret with keys `ca.crt` and `ca.key`\n- Server cert: stored in `mongodb-tls-cert` secret with key `server.pem` (contains both cert and private key concatenated)\n- Current server cert expires in 2 days (Jun 24-26 2026), needs rotation\n- Server cert has SANs for all the mongo-rs pod DNS names\n- openssl-toolbox pod is available in the mongodb namespace\n\nPlan:\n1. Extract CA cert and key from the `mongodb-tls-ca` secret into the openssl-toolbox pod\n2. Generate a new server key and CSR in the toolbox pod\n3. Sign the CSR with the CA to get a new cert valid for 365 days\n4. Update the `mongodb-tls-cert` secret with the new cert+key as `server.pem`\n5. Perform a rolling restart of the StatefulSet to pick up the new cert\n\nFor zero downtime, I'll leverage MongoDB's replica set capabilities—restarting one member at a time keeps the cluster available. I need to generate the new cert, update the secret, then trigger a rolling restart of the StatefulSet so each pod picks up the new TLS cert.\n\nNow I'll execute this in the openssl-toolbox pod, starting by extracting the CA cert and key from the secret.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7544,"cache_read_input_tokens":37741,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7544},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f54fa9d6-87ac-4510-ae5f-d86c0b2fb857","uuid":"1c57d32f-f85b-4e33-86fc-97f7d7bf50be","request_id":"req_011CcMX1MjDBaeuSgrS8zNkz"}
